{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772048174,"nonce":"eiacTIh7Nsp7+7hZWKftuCTgzVY=","title":"Add graph→tree view utility for Treescope","message":"[Imported from GitHub #42] (created 2026-01-26T17:56:53Z)\n\n## Summary\nAdd a **graph → tree view utility** that produces readable “tree-like” projections of Feedbax graphs (with cycle annotations / cut edges / optional unrolling) so Treescope (#39) can render complex models effectively.\n\n## Motivation\n- Feedbax’s outer architecture is a **graph with cycles** (feedback loops). Treescope renders PyTrees, so cyclic graphs are not directly visualizable.\n- Many graphs are “almost trees” (e.g., one feedback edge), and a **tree projection** is often the most readable view.\n- We want a principled way to generate **TreeScope-friendly views** without misrepresenting the underlying graph.\n\n## Relation to #39\n- #39 integrates Treescope for visualization.\n- This issue is about **adapting model structure into tree views** so Treescope remains useful for cyclic graphs.\n\n## Feature Proposal\nIntroduce a small utility to generate **tree projections** of graphs, plus annotations that preserve cycle information:\n\n### Core views\n1. **Cut-edge tree view**\n   - Remove cycle-forming edges (feedback edges) so the remainder is a DAG.\n   - Render the DAG as a tree (allowing duplication if needed).\n   - Attach a list of cut edges as annotations.\n\n2. **Spanning-tree view + back-edges**\n   - Pick a spanning tree rooted at a chosen node.\n   - All non-tree edges become “back-edge” annotations.\n   - Keeps all graph edges visible, but the primary structure is tree-shaped.\n\n3. **Optional unroll view (K steps)**\n   - For graphs intended to be iterated (feedback loops), provide an unrolled view for K steps.\n   - Useful for recurrent/iterated dynamics.\n\n### API sketch\n```python\n# feedbax/graph_view.py (or similar)\n\ndef graph_tree_view(\n    graph: Graph,\n    *,\n    root: str | None = None,\n    mode: Literal[\"cut\", \"spanning\", \"unroll\"] = \"cut\",\n    unroll_steps: int | None = None,\n) -\u003e TreeView:\n    \"\"\"Return a tree-shaped view plus annotations for cycles/back-edges.\"\"\"\n\n# TreeView could be a PyTree designed for Treescope rendering.\n```\n\n## Expected Benefits\n- Treescope remains useful even when models have cycles.\n- We can inspect “largest tree-like portion” of the graph without losing awareness of feedback.\n- The same utility can be used for debugging, docs, and interpretability workflows.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Provide at least one view that renders a cyclic graph in Treescope.\n- [ ] Annotate cut edges or back-edges so cycles aren’t hidden.\n- [ ] Demonstrate with a simple task-model feedback loop.\n\n---\nCo-Authored-By: GPT-5 \u003cnoreply@openai.com\u003e","files":null}]}